
{
  "department": "Department of Islamic Studies",
  "description": "Established in 2008, the Department of Islamic Studies envisioned evolving into a center of excellence for producing religious scholars to revitalize the spirit of Islamic thought and scientific inquiry. The curricula and syllabi are designed to provide in-depth knowledge of fundamental Islamic Sciences such as Al Quran, Al Hadith, Al Fiqh, Islamic history, Islamic thought, Seerah, Islamic culture, and Islamic civilization. The program aims to provide a thorough understanding of the fundamental sources of Islam, address present challenges, and create logical solutions for contemporary problems. The Department invites students to pursue BS, Master, and PhD programs and offers a variety of courses aimed at producing researchers capable of dealing with current and future issues. It also motivates students to work for the cause of Islam, provides quality education in Islamic thought and culture, and promotes the propagation of Islamic concepts and practices beyond cultural and geographical boundaries. Additionally, the Department helps students become acquainted with the convergence of Islam and sciences.",
